<head>
   <title> Try It Yourself </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      button {
         color: #f8f9f9;
         background: #903C56;
         padding: 15px;
         border: none;
         outline: none;
         transition-duration: 2s;
      }
      button:hover {
         color: #f8f9f9;
         background: #173459;
         padding: 15px;
         border: none;
         outline: none;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p> The <b>:hover</b> CSS pseudo-class is generally triggered when the user hovers over an element with the cursor (mouse pointer). </p>
   <p> It is commonly used in clickable elements. </p>
   
   <h3> Example: </h3>
   <button> Button </button>
   <p> Try to click or click then hold to see the effect. </p>
</body>
